</div>
</li>
<li class=""><span class="icon icon-minus collapse"></span><span class="icon icon-plus open"></span>
<div class="question"><i aria-hidden="true" class="fa fa-question-circle"></i>IS VEGAN PROTEIN POWDER SAFE TO USE WHEN PREGNANT?</div>
<div style="display: none;" class="answer">
<p>A question we’re regularly asked at Happy Way—‘Is vegan protein powder safe to use when pregnant?’.</p>
<p>This all depends on the vegan protein powder you’re using and what ingredients it contains.</p>
<p>At Happy Way, all of our protein supplements are safe for both pregnant and breastfeeding women, as they’re all-natural, organic and packed with vitamins, nutrients and antioxidants. We advise that you always check with your healthcare professional before using any supplement, including when you're pregnant and breastfeeding.</p>
<p>It’s said by experts that pregnant women or women who are nursing a newborn should consume a minimum of an additional 25 grams of protein per day. This can be challenging for some, especially when there are errands to run, appointments to attend and a little one to look after! Incorporating a vegan protein powder into your diet can help equip you with the vitamins and nutrients you need as well as provide you with a perfect on the go snack to enjoy throughout the day.</p>
